title: Blue Devil runners compete at Clarke, Chariton
text:
Buy Photo Martensdale-St. Marys Blue Devils (Photo: The Register) Buy Photo
CONNECT 1 TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE The Martensdale-St. Marys boys and girls cross country teams competed at Chariton Oct. 1 and at Clarke Sept. 29.
Josh Tibbits paced the boys at Chariton with a 13th-place 19:17 effort. He was followed by Jake Hill in 29th in 20:12 and Tyler McNew right behind in 30th in 20:13. Jacob Wenck finished 34th in 20:47 and Joel Criswell rounded out the team scoring in 51st in 21:59. Dakota Gibson finished 53rd in 22:22 and Zach Scovel was 55th in 22:34.
Chariton won the team title with 51 points followed by Davis County at 58 and Des Moines Christian at 66. Martensdale-St. Marys was sixth in the 10-team field at 157.
Halle Slifka led the girls with an 11th-place 24:20. Brinley White was 30th in 26:48 just in front of Tori Reynolds in 31st in 26:50. Courtney Gehringer was 55th in 36:14.
Davis County won the girls race with 78 points with Centerville second at 101 and Pleasantville third at 126. The Blue Devils did not have enough runners for a team score.
Tibbits finished in the top 10 at Clarke on Sept. 29 with a ninth-place 18:58. Hill was 22nd in 20:00, Wenck was 41st in 21:09, McNew was 42nd in 21:10 and Criswell was 43rd in 21:17 as the Blue Devils finished in a pack. Scovel rounded out the team scoring in 48th in 21:46. Gibson crossed the finish line in 51st in 22:02.
As a team, the Blue Devils finished sixth with 149 points in the 11-squad field. Davis County won at 51 points with Interstate 35 second at 64 and Albia third at 79.
Slifka led the the girls with a 10th-place 24:38 followed by Brinley in 35th in 27:33, Haley Hart in 61st in 32:46 and Gehringer in 68th in 37:57.
